A father from Arizona, whose baby boy died when he left him in a car outside a bar, was sentenced to four years in prison on Friday.

Daniel Bryant Gray had pleaded guilty to manslaughter and child abuse after the death of his three-month-old son Jamison.

The 31-year-old had left the baby strapped into a car for several hours on August 28 last year, when temperatures reached 100F.

