Gray tried fanning the infant, whose core temperature was determined to have reached 107 degrees. Employees and emergency workers tried CPR on the child, but he was later pronounced dead.

Investigators described Gray as distraught and emotional throughout his police interview.

He had been facing a possible prison term of up to 16 years, but had the maximum term reduced as part of a plea deal.

The baby's mother, Rebecca Hillary, was heartbroken by Jamison's death.

'He was my everything. I loved being a mommy,' Hillary told CBS 5 shortly after the death. 'He was a very happy boy. He was always such a good boy. He loved to smile. He just loved to smile, and play and bounce.'

